- **CLI Commands**:
  - `npx create-next-app@latest my-supabase-app`
  - `npm install @supabase/supabase-js`

- **Latest Versions**:
  - Next.js: 13.5
  - Supabase Client: 2.0.0

- **Key Config Options**:
  - Supabase URL and Anon Key in `.env.local`
    ```plaintext
    SUPABASE_URL=https://your-supabase-url.supabase.co
    SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
    ```
  - Storage Bucket Name: Define in Supabase dashboard under Storage section.

- **Example Code Snippets**:
  - Uploading an image to Supabase Storage:
    ```javascript
    import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

    const supabaseUrl = process.env.SUPABASE_URL;
    const supabaseAnonKey = process.env.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY;
    const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseAnonKey);

    async function uploadImage(file) {
      const { data, error } = await supabase.storage
        .from('your-bucket-name')
        .upload('path/to/file', file);
      if (error) throw error;
      return data;
    }
    ```
  - Displaying an image from Supabase Storage:
    ```javascript
    import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

    const supabaseUrl = process.env.SUPABASE_URL;
    const supabaseAnonKey = process.env.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY;
    const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseAnonKey);

    async function getImageUrl(publicId) {
      const { data, error } = await supabase.storage
        .from('your-bucket-name')
        .createSignedUrl(`path/to/${publicId}`, 3600);
      if (error) throw error;
      return data.signedURL;
    }
    ```
